content.description: The face of this jaggered crack-face heats with the morning sun.  It is harder than it looks.  You may find yourself sitting down on this one.  There is a traverse pitch going up and left to get out of here onto the walk off ledge but rapping from the anchors at the top of the first pitch will save you some time.
content.location: To the right of center of the Orange Wall and to the right of From My Quiver

content.description: This route follows on one of the jutting corners of the Orange Wall.  The line use several of parallel cracks on the steep ascent.
content.protection: Friend to 4", nuts and a few qd's.
content.location: About in the middle of the Orange Wall.

climbs.name: Booty Hideout
climbs.fa: backoff gear found? Baxtrum, Horning and Jones

content.description: The dead vertical hand crack leads to an arete with several bolts to anchors.  You can rapp or continue to near summit and walk off to saddle on north side.
content.protection: friends of the undulating handcrack size and several qd's
content.location: Walk along Orange Wall base to the left angling side climbing through a boulder field about half way from the east side.

content.description: On the east end of the Orange Wall are three promising lines with anchors bolts on the summit and maybe some in-line bolts
content.protection: may need more bolts otherwise nut and smaller to small cams
content.location: near very east end of the Orange Wall

pathTokens: Curtis Gulch and La Bonte Canyon
